name: Kern Public Health
tweet: Our healthcare & emergency response systems continue to be impacted by the pandemic. Kern continues to experience high volumes of 911 calls, taxing our system. We urge residents to call 911 only in a true emergency such as a heart attack, stroke or other serious health condition.  https://t.co/CRsnPGooak

name: Kern Public Health
tweet: CDC recommends everyone ages 18 yrs & older get a COVID-19 booster shot.  The risk of severe COVID-19 illness increases with age.   You can get your booster:  - 6 months after a 2-dose vaccine (Moderna or Pfizer) - 2 months after J&J.  More:  https://t.co/auiKhyLuIK.  https://t.co/MycuhnV2bG
